{"type":"message","id":"a42dfa0b","parentId":"7f13c0fb","timestamp":"2026-03-16T15:59:24.723Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"exec:52","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[?25l[2J[m[H]0;管理员: C:\\Windows\\System32\\WindowsPowerShell\\v1.0\\powershell.exe[?25h\n\n(Command exited with code 1)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":1,"durationMs":1198,"aggregated":"[?25l[2J[m[H]0;管理员: C:\\Windows\\System32\\WindowsPowerShell\\v1.0\\powershell.exe[?25h\n\n(Command exited with code 1)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773676764710}}
{"type":"message","id":"1f14c6b1","parentId":"a42dfa0b","timestamp":"2026-03-16T15:59:27.283Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec:53","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd $env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\workspace; $env:Path = [Environment]::GetEnvironmentVariable(\"Path\", \"Machine\") + \";\" + [Environment]::GetEnvironmentVariable(\"Path\", \"User\"); python skills/openclaw-tavily-search/scripts/tavily_search.py --query \"OpenClaw AI assistant\" --max-results 5 --format md","pty":true}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"moonshot","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":171,"output":99,"cacheRead":34560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34830,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773676764724}}
{"type":"message","id":"1c634196","parentId":"1f14c6b1","timestamp":"2026-03-16T15:59:29.968Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"exec:53","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[?25l[2J[m[H]0;管理员: C:\\Windows\\System32\\WindowsPowerShell\\v1.0\\powershell.exe[?25h1. OpenClaw (AI assistant gateway) now available on ...\r\n   https://www.reddit.com/r/unRAID/comments/1qv4tky/openclaw_ai_assistant_gateway_now_available_on/\r\n   - # OpenClaw (AI assistant gateway) now available on Community Apps. OpenClaw is now available as an official Community Apps template! This is my first CA template contribution, and I want to give a special thank you to the Unraid SelfHosters team for their guidance and feedback throughout the review process. They helped me get this delivered to the community the right way. People are going to run this on Unraid whether there's an official template or not. I just wanted to try and help the part of the community that wanted to get this running, as I saw there was a need here on Reddit, and in the Unraid forums. I'm just the template maintainer, not the OpenClaw developer. I can help with Unraid-specific setup issues, but core application bugs should go to the main project. However, I can always try to help. Happy to answer any questions about the template or my setup!\r\n2. OpenClaw\r\n   https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenClaw\r\n   - **OpenClaw** (formerly **Clawdbot,** **Moltbot,** and **Molty**) is a free and open-source autonomous artificial intelligence agent developed by Peter Steinberger. At the same time as the first rebranding, entrepreneur Matt Schlicht launched Moltbook—a social networking service which was intended to be used by AI agents such as OpenClaw. In March 2026, Chinese authorities restricted state-run enterprises and government agencies from running OpenClaw AI apps on office computers in order to defuse potential security risks. In February 2026, news coverage highlighted a consent-related incident involving OpenClaw and MoltMatch, an experimental dating platform where AI agents can create profiles and interact on behalf of human users. \"From Clawdbot to Moltbot to OpenClaw: Meet the AI agent generating buzz and fear globally\". \"OpenClaw Is the Hot New AI Agent, But Is It Safe to Use?\". \"Personal AI Agents like OpenClaw Are a Security Nightmare\". \"Chinese tech hubs promote OpenClaw AI agents despite scrutiny warnings\". \"Lobster buffet: China's tech firms feast on OpenClaw as companies race to deploy AI agents\".\r\n3. Use OpenClaw to Make a Personal AI Assistant\r\n   https://towardsdatascience.com/use-openclaw-to-make-a-personal-ai-assistant/\r\n   - Learn how to set up OpenClaw as a personalized AI agent. OpenClaw is essentially a system that runs Claude Code indefinitely, allowing you to set it up as your personal AI assistant. In this article, I’ll take you through how I’ve set up OpenClaw on my own system, ensuring the implementation is both secure and makes me more effective as an engineer. Learn how to set up OpenClaw as a personalized AI agent. After you’ve set up OpenClaw with Claude Code, you should personalize it. After you’ve set up OpenClaw with its personality, you should start by giving it access to stuff. Another incredibly important part of setting up OpenClaw is the skills you provided. You can simply set up OpenClaw for free,e given t\r\n[29;120Hthat you already have a Claude Code subscription. When setting up OpenClaw, you should set it up on a separate Docker con\r\n[29;120Hntainer,s isolating each environment and making sure different agents don’t have access to each other’s information and k\r\n[29;120Hkeys.\r\n4. What is OpenClaw? Your Open-Source AI Assistant for 2026\r\n   https://www.digitalocean.com/resources/articles/what-is-openclaw\r\n   - Rather than offering another chatbot, OpenClaw delivers a true personal AI agent that runs locally, remembers conte\r\n[29;120Hext across conversations, and can actually do things on your machine. * OpenClaw is a viral open-source AI assistant that\r\n[29;120Ht acts as a proactive personal agent, connecting AI models with your local files and messaging apps like WhatsApp and Dis\r\n[29;120Hscord to automate tasks around the clock. OpenClaw (affectionately called “Molty”) is a viral open-source personal AI age\r\n[29;120Hent with [68,000 GitHub stars](https://github.com/moltbot/moltbot) (and counting), created by PSPDFKit founder [Peter Ste\r\n[29;120Heinberger](https://steipete.me/). While many developers are talking about [buying Mac Minis](https://www.starryhope.com/m\r\n[29;120Hminipcs/clawdbot-mac-mini-ai-agent-trend/) to run their own instances of OpenClaw, there’s no need to make the investment\r\n[29;120Ht of hundreds of dollars in physical hardware to get started today. Check out our tutorial to learn [how to run OpenClaw]\r\n[29;120H](/community/tutorials/how-to-run-openclaw) using safe defaults with DigitalOcean’s security-hardened [1-Click OpenClaw D\r\n[29;120HDeploy](https://marketplace.digitalocean.com/apps/moltbot). Quickly deploy an always-on instance of OpenClaw using a Digi\r\n[29;120HitalOcean [1-Click OpenClaw Deploy](https://marketplace.digitalocean.com/apps/moltbot), which features a hardened securit\r\n[29;120Hty image, starting at $24/month.\r\n5. OpenClaw is an open-source AI agent that runs your computer\r\n   https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/moltbot-is-an-open-source-ai-agent-that-runs-your-computer/\r\n   - [Skip to main content](https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/moltbot-is-an-open-source-ai-agent-that-runs-your\r\n[29;120Hr-computer/#main). [Scientific American](https://www.scientificamerican.com/). When a friend messaged me two days ago abo\r\n[29;120Hout Clawdbot—a new [open-source AI agent](https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/the-ai-future-is-here/) that has sin\r\n[29;120Hnce been renamed OpenClaw—I expected yet another disappointing “assistant.” But it was already a viral sensation, with [s\r\n[29;120Hsocial media](https://www.scientificamerican.com/social-media/) testimonies calling it “[AI with hands](https://www.scien\r\n[29;120Hntificamerican.com/article/bytedance-launches-doubao-real-time-ai-voice-assistant-for-phones/)” because it actually inter\r\n[29;120Hracts with your [files and software](https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/trump-orders-genesis-mission-to-advance-a\r\n[29;120Hai-breakthroughs/). OpenClaw is free and lives locally [on your device](https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/ai-cha\r\n[29;120Hatbots-shown-to-sway-voters-raising-new-fears-about-election-influence/). I picked “Cy,” “AI assistant” and “sharp and ef\r\n[29;120Hfficient.” I chose Claude, Anthropic’s flagship AI model, as its brain ([ChatGPT is also an option](https://www.scientifi\r\n[29;120Hicamerican.com/article/new-research-shows-how-ai-could-transform-math-physics-cancer-research-and/)). He was sitting in a\r\n[29;120Ha sauna he’d installed under his stairs, [texting with his OpenClaw](https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/the-rise-\r\n[29;120H-of-ai-chatfishing-in-online-dating-poses-a-modern-turing-test/), “Samantha.” The assistant was [generating an audiobook]\r\n[29;120H](https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/survey-results-show-people-prefer-more-human-involvement-in-ai-driven-art/) \r\n[29;120H for him. OpenClaw gives that model so-called hands (or claws) so it can run commands and [manipulate files](https://www.\r\n[29;120H.scientificamerican.com/article/tests-that-ais-often-fail-and-humans-ace-could-pave-the-way-for-artificial/). *   [About]\r\n[29;120H](https://www.scientificamerican.com/page/about-scientific-american/). *   [Use of cookies/Do not sell my data](https://w\r\n[29;120Hwww.scientificamerican.com/article/moltbot-is-an-open-source-ai-agent-that-runs-your-computer/#)."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2679,"aggregated":"[?25l[2J[m[H]0;管理员: C:\\Windows\\System32\\WindowsPowerShell\\v1.0\\powershell.exe[?25h1. OpenClaw (AI assistant gateway) now available on ...\r\n   https://www.reddit.com/r/unRAID/comments/1qv4tky/openclaw_ai_assistant_gateway_now_available_on/\r\n   - # OpenClaw (AI assistant gateway) now available on Community Apps. OpenClaw is now available as an official Community Apps template! This is my first CA template contribution, and I want to give a special thank you to the Unraid SelfHosters team for their guidance and feedback throughout the review process. They helped me get this delivered to the community the right way. People are going to run this on Unraid whether there's an official template or not. I just wanted to try and help the part of the community that wanted to get this running, as I saw there was a need here on Reddit, and in the Unraid forums. I'm just the template maintainer, not the OpenClaw developer. I can help with Unraid-specific setup issues, but core application bugs should go to the main project. However, I can always try to help. Happy to answer any questions about the template or my setup!\r\n2. OpenClaw\r\n   https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenClaw\r\n   - **OpenClaw** (formerly **Clawdbot,** **Moltbot,** and **Molty**) is a free and open-source autonomous artificial intelligence agent developed by Peter Steinberger. At the same time as the first rebranding, entrepreneur Matt Schlicht launched Moltbook—a social networking service which was intended to be used by AI agents such as OpenClaw. In March 2026, Chinese authorities restricted state-run enterprises and government agencies from running OpenClaw AI apps on office computers in order to defuse potential security risks. In February 2026, news coverage highlighted a consent-related incident involving OpenClaw and MoltMatch, an experimental dating platform where AI agents can create profiles and interact on behalf of human users. \"From Clawdbot to Moltbot to OpenClaw: Meet the AI agent generating buzz and fear globally\". \"OpenClaw Is the Hot New AI Agent, But Is It