d “Molty”) is a viral open-source personal AI age\r\n[29;120Hent with [68,000 GitHub stars](https://github.com/moltbot/moltbot) (and counting), created by PSPDFKit founder [Peter Ste\r\n[29;120Heinberger](https://steipete.me/). While many developers are talking about [buying Mac Minis](https://www.starryhope.com/m\r\n[29;120Hminipcs/clawdbot-mac-mini-ai-agent-trend/) to run their own instances of OpenClaw, there’s no need to make the investment\r\n[29;120Ht of hundreds of dollars in physical hardware to get started today. Check out our tutorial to learn [how to run OpenClaw]\r\n[29;120H](/community/tutorials/how-to-run-openclaw) using safe defaults with DigitalOcean’s security-hardened [1-Click OpenClaw D\r\n[29;120HDeploy](https://marketplace.digitalocean.com/apps/moltbot). Quickly deploy an always-on instance of OpenClaw using a Digi\r\n[29;120HitalOcean [1-Click OpenClaw Deploy](https://marketplace.digitalocean.com/apps/moltbot), which features a hardened securit\r\n[29;120Hty image, starting at $24/month.\r\n5. OpenClaw is an open-source AI agent that runs your computer\r\n   https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/moltbot-is-an-open-source-ai-agent-that-runs-your-computer/\r\n   - [Skip to main content](https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/moltbot-is-an-open-source-ai-agent-that-runs-your\r\n[29;120Hr-computer/#main). [Scientific American](https://www.scientificamerican.com/). When a friend messaged me two days ago abo\r\n[29;120Hout Clawdbot—a new [open-source AI agent](https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/the-ai-future-is-here/) that has sin\r\n[29;120Hnce been renamed OpenClaw—I expected yet another disappointing “assistant.” But it was already a viral sensation, with [s\r\n[29;120Hsocial media](https://www.scientificamerican.com/social-media/) testimonies calling it “[AI with hands](https://www.scien\r\n[29;120Hntificamerican.com/article/bytedance-launches-doubao-real-time-ai-voice-assistant-for-phones/)” because it actually inter\r\n[29;120Hracts with your [files and software](https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/trump-orders-genesis-mission-to-advance-a\r\n[29;120Hai-breakthroughs/). OpenClaw is free and lives locally [on your device](https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/ai-cha\r\n[29;120Hatbots-shown-to-sway-voters-raising-new-fears-about-election-influence/). I picked “Cy,” “AI assistant” and “sharp and ef\r\n[29;120Hfficient.” I chose Claude, Anthropic’s flagship AI model, as its brain ([ChatGPT is also an option](https://www.scientifi\r\n[29;120Hicamerican.com/article/new-research-shows-how-ai-could-transform-math-physics-cancer-research-and/)). He was sitting in a\r\n[29;120Ha sauna he’d installed under his stairs, [texting with his OpenClaw](https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/the-rise-\r\n[29;120H-of-ai-chatfishing-in-online-dating-poses-a-modern-turing-test/), “Samantha.” The assistant was [generating an audiobook]\r\n[29;120H](https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/survey-results-show-people-prefer-more-human-involvement-in-ai-driven-art/) \r\n[29;120H for him. OpenClaw gives that model so-called hands (or claws) so it can run commands and [manipulate files](https://www.\r\n[29;120H.scientificamerican.com/article/tests-that-ais-often-fail-and-humans-ace-could-pave-the-way-for-artificial/). *   [About]\r\n[29;120H](https://www.scientificamerican.com/page/about-scientific-american/). *   [Use of cookies/Do not sell my data](https://w\r\n[29;120Hwww.scientificamerican.com/article/moltbot-is-an-open-source-ai-agent-that-runs-your-computer/#).","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773676769964}}
